parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle pulley can cause instant loss of power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Fuel pump leaks can cause gasoline to spray on the motorcycle, engine, and rider, leading to a high risk of fire or explosion.
symptoms: spray of gasoline on the motorcycle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel level sensor can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to unexpected stalling or running out of fuel, which can be dangerous, especially on busy highways.
symptoms: Fuel gauge shows incorrect fuel level
running out of fuel without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS pump motor can cause the brake failure light to come on, and in some cases, lead to brake lock-up, which can result in accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The brake failure light comes on
the brake pedal pulsates or feels spongy
the vehicle is unable to stop properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The improper surface tempering of the brake disk can cause unpredictable brake pulsing, leading to unsafe braking conditions and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The rear brake pulsates unpredictably upon application
the brakes are uneven or grabby.
